Hi! I have created a signature for an empty message with that private key using o1js.
I am trying to recreate the same signature using Rust to make sure they work in the same way. 

However it doesn't create the same signature. 

What can I change to make it create the same signature?

```rs
#[cfg(test)]
mod test {
    use mina_hasher::{Hashable, ROInput};
    use mina_signer::{create_kimchi, Keypair, SecKey, Signer};

    #[derive(Clone)]
    struct Msg {}

    impl Hashable for Msg {
        type D = ();
        fn to_roinput(&self) -> ROInput {
            ROInput::new()
        }
        fn domain_string(_: Self::D) -> Option<String> {
            None
        }
    }

    #[test]
    fn test() {
        let seckey =
            SecKey::from_base58("EKEe6PQLoMoJdXnH3E9NhaRRgXVzJKS5tTub1F1V57orjKj9Nf1p").unwrap();

        let keypair = Keypair::from_secret_key(seckey).unwrap();

        let mut signer = create_kimchi::<Msg>(());

        let signature = signer.sign(&keypair, &Msg {});

        assert_eq!(
            signature.rx.to_string(),
            r#"Fp256 "(28AC9A5B148ACBDA5B5F02CF5585C82DA5364E59F21E64AB2F45E357AE059D0F)"#
        );

        assert_eq!(
            signature.s.to_string(),
            r#"Fp256 "(3ADA579F0E393F68D46F511F4E90A40CB77C6D8435EFDF6F93920573ADDBC509)"#
        );
    }
}
```

Here is the logic of `Signature.create`: <https://github.com/o1-labs/o1js/blob/95e5d419e86be95c5fd4803d6679e2ea6aaaaea3/src/lib/signature.ts#L254>

```js
const pk = PrivateKey.fromBase58("EKEacPme92tT4NSpbuhdswJSsG7Z1qn5GLtdaRWwCtUQLfqMyAoy")
const sig = Signature.create(pk, [Field(42)])
```

# What I Do
I sign `[Field(42)]` message with `EKEacPme92tT4NSpbuhdswJSsG7Z1qn5GLtdaRWwCtUQLfqMyAoy` private key.

- Message: `[Field(42)]`
- Public Key: `B62qoTFrus93Ryi1VzbFakzErBBmcikHEq27vhMkU4FfjGfCovv41fb`
- Private Key: `EKEacPme92tT4NSpbuhdswJSsG7Z1qn5GLtdaRWwCtUQLfqMyAoy`

